description:
Junior Java Developer

Columbus, OH

Contract to Hire

As the Junior Software Developer, you will support our Fortune 100 Insurance client and work on designing, coding, and testing software in modern software languages, assisting with software integration, implementing solutions, and much more. This is an exciting opportunity to get your foot in the door at one of the top companies in Columbus and gain niche technology experience. If you have a strong understanding of object-oriented programming and a degree in Computer Science & Engineering (or related), please keep reading and apply!

Responsibilities:

  • Design, code, and test software in modern software languages (e.g. Java, Angular)
  • Troubleshoot and debug released software
  • Implement and customize solutions for customers
  • Integrate software with multiple database platforms and external systems/platforms
  • Support, maintain,and document software functionality
  • Evaluate and identify new technologies for adoption

Minimum Qualifications:

  • Degree in Computer Science & Engineering, Computer Information Systems or related major
  • 0-2 years of Software Development or Testing experience through coursework, projects, internships, and/or capstone
  • Foundational understanding and willingness to learn and work with API’s
  • Desire to learn more about ETL/Informatica and MDM (master data management)
  • Experience with Java, SQL, and Object Oriented Programming
  • Driven, hard-working personality
  • Strong problem solving skills
  • Self-starter with the ability to learn quickly and work independently or as part of a team

Why Should I Apply?

  • You will get to work with new, cutting-edge technologies
  • Work in a complex space that has high business impact
  • Top Rated company to work in Columbus
  • Support a Fortune 100 insurance companies’ agent and financial data partners
  • Opportunity for long term employment and career growth in a trending space

Eight Eleven Group provides equal employment opportunities (EEO) to all employees and applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, national origin, age, sex, citizenship, disability, genetic information, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity, marital status, amnesty or status as a covered veteran in accordance with applicable federal, state, and local laws.

Job Type: Full-time

Pay: $52,000.00 - $60,000.00 per year

Schedule:

  • Monday to Friday

Ability to commute/relocate:

  • Columbus, OH 43204: Reliably commute or planning to relocate before starting work (Required)

Experience:

  • REST: 1 year (Preferred)
  • Java: 1 year (Preferred)

Work Location: Hybrid remote in Columbus, OH 43204
